\outl0\strokewidth0 Starting in the 1920's, Europeans settled in larger numbers, building a store, a post office, hotels, a dance hall, sawmills, logging camps, wharves, and farms. A fleet of passenger steamship vessels connected Sechelt to the mainland. Union Steamship Company promoted Sechelt as a resort area, bringing passengers across to their wharves in Sechelt and Selma Park. Aside from tourism, Sechelt's economy was oriented primarily towards logging and fishing.\
\
